    ∇ SYNCHCAPSGRIDS P;L;R;I;Y;M;A;B;Z;T;J;path[1]   ⍝Find differences among all grids in two CAPS paths named in ⍵[2]   ⍝Looks at paths.par and finds all grids within; compares grid[3]   ⍝size, position, and stats.[4]   ⍝Example:[5]   ⍝   SYNCHCAPSGRIDS 'D:\CAPS\ Z:\'[6]   ⍝For each directory, shows ←grids in left only, →grids in right only, ≠grids that differ[7]   ⍝B. Compton, 8 Feb 2011[8]   ⍝25 Nov 2013: use path, not pathdir, thanks to change in SETPATHS[9]   [10]  [11]  [12]   GRIDINIT ''[13]   ⎕←'Synching grids in CAPS directories'[14]   ⎕←''[15]   P←MATRIFY P[16]   path←FRDBL P[1;][17]   SETPATHS[18]   A←GETPATHS[;3]                             ⍝Left paths[19]   path←FRDBL P[2;][20]   SETPATHS[21]   B←GETPATHS[;3]                             ⍝Right paths[22]   ⎕←' ' ' ' 'Left' 'Right'⍪(GETPATHS,A)[;1 2 4 3][23]   ⎕←''[24]  [25]   I←0[26]  L1:→((⍴A)<I←I+1)/0                          ⍝For each path,[27]   L←GRIDLIST I⊃A                             ⍝   Left grids[28]   R←GRIDLIST I⊃B                             ⍝   Right grids[29]   →((0∊⍴L)^0∊⍴R)/L1                          ⍝   If any grids,[30]   Z←(0=L MATIOTA R)⌿'→',R                    ⍝      Grids in right but not left[31]   Z←Z OVER (T←0=R MATIOTA L)⌿'←',L           ⍝      and left but not right[32]   Y←(~T)⌿L                                   ⍝      grids in both[33]   J←0[34]  L2:→((1↑⍴Y)<J←J+1)/L3                       ⍝      For each grid in both,[35]   Z←Z OVER (~(1 GRIDDESCRIBE (I⊃A) PATH Y[J;])≡1 GRIDDESCRIBE (I⊃B) PATH Y[J;])⌿'≠',Y[,J;][36]   →L2[37]  L3:⎕←(I⊃A),' ←→ ',I⊃B[38]   ⎕←' ',' ',' ',40 TELPRINT Z[39]   ⎕←''[40]   →L1    ∇